rComments: He's very knowledgeable of the course material. But his lectures can be quite boring. He doesn't share his powerpoints, but most of the information is in the textbook, which is worth the buy. Attendance is important. You can tell the guy really likes what he's teaching, which is encouraging. Good prof, not great.

Un enseignant super ! Il permet aux étudiants de faire les travaux en équipe! Le test de mi-session, s'il en fait un, est réellement facile si vous avez été aux cours. L'examen final est un take home et il donne beaucoup de temps pour le faire! Très gentil et aidant si on va le rencontrer dans son bureau ! La matière est claire !!

Honestly, he is a pretty decent prof. A bit monotone at times, but he is extremely helpful if you approach him for help. The course work isn't very difficult, but if you're not very familiar with history, your readings will save you!

He was ok. His lectures are really boring which literally meant forcing myself out of bed at 8 on a Monday morning, to make it to his class. Also, the classes aren't mandatory, but you should go as the slides aren't put online. His midterm/exam were open book. As an FI student, it was kinda difficult to follow, the FLS didn't help me at all.

Good Prof.  Has forgot more about what he talking about than I will ever learn regarding History.  Just needs to clarify things when it comes to assignments (devoirs) and what he is exactly looking for

A very cute man. Sit in the front so that you can understand best. He doesn't put his slides online - or even have a profile online. There are 3 (easy) 1page resumés to write. The midterm &final were a tad ambiguous, however they were openbook. Take the time to ask him questions in private and you will benefit from it A LOT! (for papers especially)

I had this prof twice unfortunatly. He taught the same exact thing in two totally unrelated course. His lectures are very confusing and boring. I didn't anything at all. Would not recommend this prof at all.

One of the most boring lecturers I've ever had the misfortune of listening to, and he doesn't put the slides online so you HAVE to go. His assignments were pretty interesting though and he is really nice.

Un des pire prof que j'ai eu ! On voit qu'il est passionné de sa matière, mais il est très monotone et ennuyant. Il lit ses power-points qui est, en fait, le résumé des livres qu'on doit lire. Bref, il y a beaucoup de répétition. Il n'est pas clair dans ses questions de travail; j'ai du me chicané avec une fois sur ce sujet. Bref, prof à évité.
